## Definition of done

### Dependency scan
- [ ] `cargo audit` run — all Critical/High findings resolved
- [ ] `cargo deny check` run — licences, bans, and advisories clean

### Unsafe code
- [ ] `cargo geiger` run — unsafe count reviewed
- [ ] All `unsafe` blocks have `// SAFETY:` comments
- [ ] Unsafe surface area is minimised

### Cryptography (if applicable)
- [ ] Only approved algorithms in use
- [ ] No banned algorithms present
- [ ] Keys retrieved from Vault/environment (never hardcoded)
- [ ] Nonces generated with CSPRNG
- [ ] Constant-time comparisons used where required
- [ ] Secrets zeroised on drop

### Secrets
- [ ] `/rust-security:scan-secrets` run — zero secrets committed

### Supply chain
- [ ] `/rust-security:supply-chain-audit` run — findings reviewed
- [ ] New or changed dependencies reviewed for legitimacy

### Threat model
- [ ] `/rust-security:threat-model` run — new threats identified
- [ ] All STRIDE categories addressed

### Compliance report
- [ ] Compliance report generated and saved to `project-management/src/`
- [ ] All findings logged with severity, CWE mapping, and tracking issue

### Remediation
- [ ] All Critical findings resolved
- [ ] All High findings resolved
- [ ] Medium and Low findings tracked in issues with resolution targets

